    "body": "HI @LeiWang1999 \r\n\r\nI checked rocm docker file and found rocm sdk version was too old. In this PR, I upgrade rocm sdk version to be 7.2. \r\n\r\nI also added the support of RDNA4 GPU (R9700, GFX1201). using this PR, I successfully run the amd flash attention fwd example.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"879\" height=\"119\" alt=\"{4FBEBF94-F572-4052-BDDF-166B22691F77}\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7f779239-8f30-4b53-8a57-8556c5317454\" />\r\n\r\nThis PR is also tested successfully on MI300. \r\n\r\nThanks    \n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * RDNA WMMA support for accelerated GEMM on gfx11/gfx12 with new emitters and layouts.\n  * New index-mapping and emitter utilities for WMMA fragment load/store and layout inference.\n  * Runtime RDNA target detection.\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved flash-attention behavior and autotuning for RDNA GPUs.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Upgraded ROCm base image and expanded supported GPU architectures.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
